Mounting Bracket

Mounting Bracket

Timeframe:  2 days

BOM:
  • AL6061-T6 Extrusion, 1in x 4in x 5in
Equipment:
  • Milling Machine
  • Drill Bit Set
  • 1" Roughing Endmill

Stress testing reveled that the PC Build remained cool and quiet under intense workloads. To further test the limits of the build, the CPU was overclocked to 5GHz, up from the 3.7GHz base boost-clock. In the process, the ABS pump bracket warped. The warping did not result in any leaks, so a new mounting bracket was not installed until it was time to perform maintenance on the cooling system two years later. At this time, a mounting bracket was manufactured out of AL6061-T6 on a milling machine. More on this on the   mounting bracket project page.

  • The i7 8700K was launched.

    So I bought one.

  • A test bench was assmebled.

    It was confirmed that the computed booted to BIOS.

  • A mounting bracket for the pump was designed in CAD.

    The following day, the mounting bracket was 3D printed out of ABS plastic.

  • The liquid cooling loop was assembled.

    PETG tubing was cut to shape and bent to complete the liquid cooling loop.

  • The computer was finished.

    The loop was flushed with distilled water before being filled with the coolant. It was then monitored for leaks.

  • The computer was stress tested.

    Software was used to assess the performance of the PC, resulting in outstanding numbers.

  • The computer was overclocked.

    This resulted in higher temperatures which warped the plastic mounting bracket.
